The glory and disgrace of youth
Yet thus , when we our way discern
all the worth of these allow , And all their faults discern in those
that we can quell The wildest passions in their rage
Ah! Virtue , dost thou arm , when now This bold rebellious race are fled ; When all these tyrants rest , and thou Art warring with the mighty dead
thou arm , when now This bold rebellious race
nothing men can do , When chilling Age comes creeping on
for new conquests strive in vain
for new conquests strive in vain
the enjoyment will be thine , In that renewed , that endless life
